install.packages("coronavirus")
library(coronavirus)

Useful codes: Data Analysis for the USA

  1. Load necessary packages
library(tidyverse)
library(magrittr)
  1. Filter USA
usa_corona <- coronavirus %>% filter(country == "US")
  1. Extract recovered cases in the USA
recover_usa_corona <- usa_corona %>% filter(type=="recovered")
head(recover_usa_corona)
        date province country     lat     long      type cases
1 2020-01-22               US 37.0902 -95.7129 recovered     0
2 2020-01-23               US 37.0902 -95.7129 recovered     0
3 2020-01-24               US 37.0902 -95.7129 recovered     0
4 2020-01-25               US 37.0902 -95.7129 recovered     0
5 2020-01-26               US 37.0902 -95.7129 recovered     0
6 2020-01-27               US 37.0902 -95.7129 recovered     0
ggplot(recover_usa_corona, aes(x=date, y=cases)) + geom_line() + ggtitle("US: Daily Covid-19 Recoveries")

  1. Plot country
library(ggplot2)
library(maptools)
library(tibble)
library(tidyverse)
library(ggrepel)
library(png)
library(grid)
data(wrld_simpl)

p <- ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(
    data = wrld_simpl,
    aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group), fill = "thistle", colour = "white"
  ) +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(-180, 180), ylim = c(-90, 90)) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(-180, 180, 120)) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(-90, 90, 100))

p +
  geom_point(
    data = usa_corona, aes(x = long, y = lat), color = "mediumpurple1", size
    = 1
  )
